    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In the context of art and architecture, people who apply plaster, which is primarily a mixture of lime, sand, and water, to a wall, ceiling, or other surface, to which mural paintings may or may not be applied.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000008771/Roberts, Construction Industry Thesaurus (1976)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>En el contexto del arte y la arquitectura, gente qye aplica yeso, que es principalmente una mezcla de cal, arena y agua a las murallas, cielos u otras superficies, a las cuales se le puede o no aplicar pintura mural.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Personen die pleisterwerk – meestal een mengsel van kalk, zand en water – aanbrengen op muren, plafonds of andere oppervlakken, waarop vervolgens eventueel muurschilderingen worden aangebracht.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在藝術創作過程或建築工程中負責塗敷灰泥者，灰泥的主要原料為石灰、沙和水，可塗抹在牆面、天花板或其他平面上，灰泥層上可再繪以壁畫。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
